[Clearly, last week's quiet report on the polio surveillance front was the calm before the storm, with extended activity now of both the WPV and the cVDPVs. Of significance in this week's report is not only that there are 5 newly confirmed cases of WPV1 infection involving Afghanistan and Pakistan (with the Pakistan reports classified as "advanced noticed" but confirmed on the Pakistan official "Stop Polio Pakistan" website; see <Poliomyelitis update (28): Pakistan (KP) new cases, violence 20190425.6436992> for details), but also 4 separate outbreaks of cVDPV2 in Africa involving cases in the Democratic Republic of the Congo, Nigeria (including a new outbreak), and Somalia. But all of the locations of identification of polioviruses (wild and circulating vaccine-derived) involved countries with ongoing civil unrest. Unfortunately, there are other countries in the world with ongoing civil unrest. Although these have not recently reported polio cases, one can't help but wonder how good the polio vaccination efforts are permitted to be in the conflict zones, and how good the AFP surveillance may be in these conflict zones.

For a map showing the locations of cases of WPV and cVDPV, see http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/.

