******
[2] Afghanistan (Uruzgan)
Date: Tue 23 Apr 2019
Source: Xinhua [edited]
http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2019-04/23/c_138001506.htm


A fresh positive polio case affecting a 10-month girl has been detected in southern Afghan province of Uruzgan, causing concerns among the parents across the country, a local health official said Tuesday [23 Apr 2019].

"The case was discovered and registered in a remote village of Chora district, east of provincial capital Tirin Kot city, within the past week," Dr. Sayifuddin, in charge of the provincial polio-elimination program, told Xinhua.

The latest confirmed polio cases have risen to 3 so far this year [2019], while 20 polio cases were registered in the country last year [2018], according to health officials.

The ongoing insurgency and conflicts have been hindering the efforts to stamp out the infectious disease in the mountainous country.

[Byline: Xuxin (editor)

